SUMMARY:Deadline: Grove and Pines Film Festival: Erin Carine Grant for Quee
 r Creatives 2026
DESCRIPTION:Annual grant from the Grove and Pines Film Festival honouring t
 he legacy of Erin Carine\, awarded to a filmmaker whose project embodies c
 reativity\, courage and a deep commitment to authentic queer storytelling.
  ELIGIBILITY: open to individual filmmakers\; applicants do not need to ha
 ve a finished film. The public grant page does not state geographic restri
 ctions\, age limits or career-stage requirements - confirm on the linked p
 age before applying. Apply via the Google Form linked from the festival's 
 grant-info page.\n\nOrganisation: Grove and Pines Film Festival (GAPFF)\nL
 ocation: United States (festival is US-based\; geographic eligibility not 
 specified on the grant page)\nAward: $5\,000 USD grant awarded annually at
  the festival. No application fee mentioned.\nDuration: One-off project gr
 ant\n\nMore: https://www.groveandpinesfilmfestival.com/grant-info
URL:https://www.groveandpinesfilmfestival.com/grant-info
LOCATION:United States (festival is US-based\; geographic eligibility not s
 pecified on the grant page)
END:VEVENT
